https://prez.dev/description.@value: The overarching categorization of vocabularies prepared by the Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA).

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: Vocabularies related to the study of life in past geological time, based on the distribution and form of body fossils and their traces. This includes interpreting their relationships to other organisms both through time and within their original habitat (phylogeny, evolution, paleoecology), their environments (paleoenvironmental reconstruction, paleobiogeography), and the chronology of the Earth's history (biostratigraphy).
